<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module has NONE: that is the chapter's point made by the build. The gate's model types are
    immutable records (Finding, GatePolicy), the verdict is a sealed type of records (GateDecision),
    and the gate itself holds only its policy and two atomic counters, exposing no array or mutable
    collection — so the representation-exposure detectors stay quiet without any suppression. The
    filter is kept (empty) so a future, genuinely-reviewed suppression has a home with a reason,
    rather than being added inline.
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
